snippet.textDisplay: I have been a fan of Mr. Ankan Kumar Roy’s crystal-clear, old Calcutta-esque voice since his rendition of “Upo” in Hatirpool Sessions; it is great to see that he is scaling new heights by entering the Coke Studio stage. Ms. Afrin’s soulful jazz voice was also a refreshingly beautiful touch. Kudos to Mr. Shuvendu Das Shuvo and the team for constantly delivering beautifully melodic compositions — this one easily takes one back to a nostalgic era.

snippet.textDisplay: Coke Studio Bangla offers a classy and soulful experience of Bangla music in its many forms. This song, in particular, carries a magnetic charm with its heartfelt lyrics and enchanting melody.
